[30;1m1006 | [0m[35m      existing functionality of :meth:`.CacheRegion.invalidate`, means[0m
[30;1m1007 | [0m[35m      :meth:`.CacheRegion.get_or_create` will not return the "old" value at[0m

[30;1m1009 | [0m[35m      "soft" invalidation means that getters can continue to return the[0m
[30;1m1010 | [0m[35m      old value until a new one is generated.[0m

[30;1m450 | [0m[35m        distributed lock service, which is known to interfere with the lock's[0m

[30;1m72 | [0m[35mbackend also requires that the URL of the memcached server be passed within the ``arguments`` dictio[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35mThe configuration is separated into two sections.  Upon construction via :func:`.make_region`,[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35mthe :class:`.CacheRegion` object is available, typically at module[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35mimport time, for usage in decorating functions.   Additional configuration details passed to[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35m:meth:`.CacheRegion.configure` are typically loaded from a configuration file and therefore[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35mnot necessarily available until runtime, hence the two-step configurational process.[0m

[30;1m13 | [0m[35mthe invocation of the creation function by only one thread and/or process at[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35ma time, deferring all other threads/processes to the "value retrieval" function[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35muntil the single creation thread is completed.[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mDo I Need to Learn the dogpile Core API Directly?[0m

[30;1m151 | [0m[35m            self.cache[key] = value[0m

[30;1m1004 | [0m[35m      The :meth:`.CacheRegion.invalidate` method now supports an option[0m
[30;1m1005 | [0m[35m      ``hard=True|False``.  A "hard" invalidation, equivalent to the[0m
[30;1m1006 | [0m[35m      existing functionality of :meth:`.CacheRegion.invalidate`, means[0m
[30;1m1007 | [0m[35m      :meth:`.CacheRegion.get_or_create` will not return the "old" value at[0m
[30;1m1008 | [0m[35m      all, forcing all getters to regenerate or wait for a regeneration.[0m
[30;1m1009 | [0m[35m      "soft" invalidation means that getters can continue to return the[0m
[30;1m1010 | [0m[35m      old value until a new one is generated.[0m
[30;1m1011 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m107 | [0m[35m        Added new method :meth:`.CacheRegion.get_value_metadata` which can be used[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m        to get a value from the cache along with its metadata, including timestamp[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m        of when the value was cached.  The :class:`.CachedValue` object is returned[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m        which features new accessors to retrieve cached time and current age. Pull[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m        request courtesy Grégoire Deveaux.[0m

[30;1m42 | [0m[35m``dogpile`` provides the concept of a "dogpile lock", a control structure[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35mwhich allows a single thread of execution to be selected as the "creator" of[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35msome resource, while allowing other threads of execution to refer to the previous[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mversion of this resource as the creation proceeds; if there is no previous[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mDogpile consists of two subsystems, one building on top of the other.[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m``dogpile`` provides the concept of a "dogpile lock", a control structure[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mwhich allows a single thread of execution to be selected as the "creator" of[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35msome resource, while allowing other threads of execution to refer to the previous[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mversion of this resource as the creation proceeds; if there is no previous[0m
